# Model Layer Standards

Werewolf models are defined in `@werewolf/game-engine` (`packages/game-engine/src/werewolf/models/`). Do not create `src/models/`; client architecture/contract tests belong in `src/__tests__`.

## Rules

- Declarative content (spec / schema / types / enums / constants), pure function queries/factories (`getRoleSpec()`, `makeActionTarget()`, type guard `isActionTarget()`).
- Importing services / hooks / UI / contexts / navigation is forbidden. Side effects (IO / network / audio / Alert / `console.*`) are forbidden. Runtime business logic (state transitions, resolver calculations, death calculation) is forbidden.

## Role Specs Table-Driven Source Of Truth

| Source       | File            | Responsibility                                                             |
| ------------ | --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `ROLE_SPECS` | `spec/specs.ts` | Role intrinsic attributes, ability declarations, UI metadata, night steps  |
| Step order   | `spec/plan.ts`  | Night-1 stable step order through `NIGHT_STEP_ORDER_INTERNAL`              |
| Model types  | `spec/*.ts`     | Type definitions for ability, plan, schema, role spec, and structured text |

- Step id = stable `SchemaId`. UI text as logic key is forbidden. `audioKey` lives in each `ROLE_SPECS[*].nightSteps[*]`.
- Input validity is written in role abilities and `nightSteps[*].ui`; resolver validation must match those declarations. Cross-night constraints (`previousActions` / `lastNightTarget` etc.) are forbidden.
- Attack neutrality: can attack any seat (including self/wolf teammates), no `notSelf` / `notWolf` added.
- Wolf visibility uses role `recognition` fields; do not create another parallel wolf-meeting model.
